<h3>Short Scale Bass, With A Road-Worn Finish</h3>
JMJ is known by many as a true renaissance man of the modern music scene, having played alongside Beck, along with the likes of Nine Inch Nails, Jimmy Eat World, Paramore and many more besides.

With this signature Mustang Bass, Fender have managed to create an instrument that's ideal for today's breed of multi-genre musicians.
<h4>Fender JMJ Road Worn Mustang Bass RW Black Highlights</h4>
<ul>
 	<li>Signature bass for multi-genre bassplayer Justin Meldal-Johnson</li>
 	<li>Shorter-scale, Mustang Bass body and neck design</li>
 	<li>Lightweight Alder body, with aÂ road worn Nitro LacquerÂ Black finish</li>
